      • MessageListener

        public MessageListener(ConnectionParameters connectionParameters,
               int prefetchCount)
                throws IOException
        Convenience constructor that uses a default ObjectMapper and the DefaultMessageRegistry but allows setting of the prefetch count (the RabbitMQ QOS).
        The prefetch count is how many records a channel will batch consume at a time. Thus if there are long running consumers, and slow message throughput, one might opt to run a low prefetch count (like 1), in order to allow other channels to consume messages. This blog is worth reading before opting to change the default prefetch count http://www.rabbitmq.com/blog/2012/05/11/some-queuing-theory-throughput-latency-and-bandwidth/
        Throws:
        IOException

      • listen

        public <T> void listen(String queue,
              String routingKey,
              String exchange,
              int numberOfThreads,
              MessageCallback<T> callback)
            throws IOException
        Can be used to listen for a certain type of message. Prior to registering the callback it will declare the exchange and queue and bind the queue to the exchange using the provided routing key. The callback will be automatically invoked for each new message. Each message will be acknowledged as soon as the message is delivered (not processed). Uses the default prefetch count (messages to prefetch from the queue).
        Type Parameters:
        T - of the message
        Parameters:
        queue - to bind to
        routingKey - to use to bind the queue to the exchange
        exchange - to bind to
        numberOfThreads - the number of threads to use to process messages for this callback in parallel
        callback - to execute
        Throws:
        IOException - if there was any communication exception
